<title>Introduction to Evolution</title>

<p><app>Evolution</app> is a personal information management application that combines email client 
features with calendar, address book, to-do list and notes, in one place.</p>

<p>By default, <app>Evolution</app> opens the <gui>Mail</gui> view where you can <link xref="check-mail">check your mail</link>. If your mail is not there, you can use the <link xref="assistant">assistant</link> to configure it. 
You can switch to the <gui>Calendar</gui> view to <link xref="conf-appointment">make an appointment</link>, 
or to the <gui>Contact</gui> view to <link xref="add-contact">save your contacts</link>, 
or to the <gui>Task</gui> view to <link xref="add-memo">plan a to-do list</link>,
or to the <gui>Memo</gui> view to <link xref="add-memo">add a task</link>.</p>

<note style="advanced">
 <p>When Evolution starts, it remembers the last view that you used. 
    You can click on the specific view to start to work. </p>
 <p>These views are placed in the bottom of the left in the window (the so-called "switcher").</p>
</note>

